<title>José Silvestre White, Afro-Cuban Composer, Violinist & Professor</title>
<meta name="keywords" content="Afro-Cuban composer, Afro-Cuban violinist, La Bella Cubana, Violin Concerto in F-sharp Minor, Cedille 90000 035 (1997)">
<meta name="description" content="José Silvestre White (1836-1918) was an Afro-Cuban composer, violinist and professor at the Paris Conservatory of Music. He was born in Matanzas, Cuba. Probably his most famous composition is the habanera &quot;La Bella cubana&quot;. White's Violin Concerto in F-sharp Minor (21:24), dating from 1864, is available on Cedille 90000 035 (1997).">
